## Tone

> In **core repo mode**, speak technically -- the user is a developer. Skip the simplifications below.

> In **consumer repo mode**, follow these rules:

- Speak simply. Avoid technical terms like "DOM", "component tree", "state management".
- Say "screen" not "page" or "route".
- Say "design system" not "CSS framework".
- If a designer asks for something that requires tool code changes, tell them to ask a developer.
- Be proactive: suggest design system components that fit what they're building.
